  "title": "HVAC Project Engineer (Pharmaceutical & GMP Facilities / 5.5 Days)",
  "description": "<p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p><ul><li>Lead and support HVAC design for industrial projects (pharmaceutical, semiconductor, data center, food, chemical, and new energy) in Singapore and overseas<br />Develop HVAC design deliverables independently from Concept Design (CD) to Detailed Design (DD) stages</li><li>Prepare key documents such as URS, load calculations, airflow diagrams, zoning, pressurization layouts, and HVAC design reports</li><li>Produce or review duct layouts, detailed drawings, shop drawings, and 3D models (Revit / SketchUp)</li><li>Coordinate and manage LDIs, PEs, and QPs during design and project execution</li><li>Support procurement activities including BOQ preparation, value engineering, tender documents, and technical bid evaluations</li><li>Review consultant and subcontractor submissions for compliance with GMP, URS, and applicable codes and standards</li><li>Provide site construction and commissioning support when required</li><li>Support FM / LEED design consultancy activities</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p></p></p><ul><li>6-10 years of relevant HVAC design experience with pharmaceutical project experiences</li><li>Proficient in AutoCAD, Revit, Navisworks, CFD, and related engineering tools</li><li>Knowledge of FDA/cGMP, ISO 14644, ASHRAE, and local/international building codes</li><li>Strong understanding of HVAC system and material selection</li><li>Good communication skills, teamwork mindset, and ability to work independently</li><li>Willing to travel overseas for short-term assignments</li></ul><p><br />GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd | EA Licence 11C3793 | EA Personnel: Novita Widjaja | Registration No: R22105960<br /><br /><em>This is in partnership with the Employment and Employability Institute Pte Ltd (“e2i”).</em></p><p><em>e2i is the empowering network for workers and employers seeking employment and employability solutions. e2i serves as a bridge between workers and employers, connecting with workers to offer job security through job-matching, career guidance and skills upgrading services, and partnering employers to address their manpower needs through recruitment, training, and job redesign solutions. e2i is a tripartite initiative of the National Trades Union Congress set up to support nation-wide manpower and skills upgrading initiatives.</em></p><p><em>By applying for this role, you consent to GMP Recruitment Services (S) Pte Ltd’s </em><a href=\"https://www.gmprecruit.com/legal/privacy-policy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">PDPA</a><em> and </em><a href=\"https://us-west-2.protection.sophos.com?d=e2i.com.sg&u=aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZTJpLmNvbS5zZy9wZHBhLw==&i=NThlNDdhOGMyYmI5N2YwZmQxZDk4NjQw&t=cWdqRFV0Uy80RjN3MDlSYmM1dS85VTRxVTRoYVlXdWFyWTYzaGlVS3k0TT0=&h=1ad0460f503340658fbeab159c31256f&s=AVNPUEhUT0NFTkNSWVBUSVaVGQEVMuPAipiPENS4aadnRg3RqoiWpHBKgNtumWhHjA\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>e2i’s PDPA</em></a><em>.</em></p>",
